    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Galveston</placeName>
                <date>Jany. 20<hi rend="sup">Th</hi> 1855</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>Saturday</date> Night</p>
            <p>My esteemed friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I avail myself of the earliest<lb/> opportunity to express my
                sincere acknow-<lb/>ledgements for the very kind notice you<lb/> have taken of my
                melancholy request con-<lb/>veyed in the few lines I addressed you<lb/>
                <date>Nov. 15th</date>. The <date>Jany</date>. Number of the “Occident”<lb/> arrived
                to-day, wherein my dear sister and self<lb/> read with deep emotion the very <hi
                    rend="underline">appropriate</hi><lb/> and <hi rend="underline">feeling
                    tribute</hi> you have paid to the mem-<lb/>ory of our loved departed ones. It
                elicited<lb/> feelings of gratitude towards you that I<lb/> would willingly convey
                to paper, but I<lb/> know that I could not do justice to you, or<lb/> myself in
                attempting to express them.<lb/> I must therefore beg you kind friend, to<lb/>
                receive my assurance, that <hi rend="underline">we both</hi> entertain<lb/>
                sentiments of high regard for you, and<lb/> shall never be unmindful of the
                strong<lb/> and satisfactory proof you have given us</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>of your friendly consideration. In all<lb/> probability, with God's will, we
                will<lb/> shortly be in your city, when I trust<lb/> to be enabled to express in
                stronger terms<lb/> how much we appreciate the favor confer-<lb/>red. Hoping that
                you derived ben-<lb/>efit from your western tour, and that<lb/> these few lines will
                find you in the<lb/> enjoyment of health, with the combined<lb/> regards of my
                beloved sister, and<lb/> brother-in-law, I remain dear sir<lb/> your sincerely
                obliged friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">Hannah Dyer</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
        </body>
